info.description: The Billogram API is built according to RESTful principles, which means it uses HTTP as an application protocol rather than just as a transport layer for a custom protocol, like SOAP does. In other words, HTTP features such as the various request types (GET, PUT, POST, DELETE), response codes (403 Forbidden, 404 Not Found, 500 Internal Server Error) and standard headers (Accept, Authorization, Cache-Control) are a part of the API.
info.title: Swagger Invoice/Billogram

mode.description: Credit type, amount requires the amount field

amount.description: Only required when mode is amount, should not be present in the other modes. The amount to credit the billogram by, given in the invoicing currency. Please note that the absence of the amount field when mode is amount will result in a full credit.
amount.x-ms-summary: Only required when mode is amount, should not be present in the other modes. The amount to credit the billogram by, given in the invoicing currency. Please note that the absence of the amount field when mode is amount will result in a full credit.

method.description: Can be one of the following: Email, SMS, Letter or Efaktura. If left out, the same method as the original invoice will be used.
method.x-ms-summary: Can be one of the following: Email, SMS, Letter or Efaktura. If left out, the same method as the original invoice will be used.

post.description: Credit part, remaining or the full billogram.

id.description: Unique ID of the billogram. Can be used to fetch the full billogram object.

invoice_no.description: Number on the latest main invoice on the billogram. Will return a null value if the billogram is not attested yet. If you've set invoice_no yourself and need to know the value of an unattested billogram, you will have to get the data for that specific object.

state.description: Current state of the billogram. See the section on billogram states for details of the values that can occur here.

flags.description: Details of the current state of the billogram

invoice_date.description: Invoice date printed on the invoice. Given as an ISO 8601 date string.

due_date.description: Due-by date for the invoice. Given as an ISO 8601 date string.

currency.description: Currency the invoice is billed in.

ocr_number.description: OCR number for electronic bank payment of the invoice.

remaining_sum.description: Amount left to be paid by the customer, given in the invoicing currency, including the calculated VAT.

total_sum.description: The total amount the customer has been ordered to pay, given in the invoicing currency, including the calculated VAT.

created_at.description: Timestamp the billogram object was first created at. Given as a date-time string in UTC.

updated_at.description: Timestamp the billogram object was last updated at. Given as a date-time string in UTC.

items.description: Array of items as invoice rows on the Billogram Invoice.

customer_no.description: Customer number of the recipient of the billogram. This field is required when creating a billogram, and becomes read-only after the billogram object has been created. (It is not possible to change which customer a billogram was sent to.)

org_no.description: Organisational or personal number of the customer, depending on the customer type.

name.description: Name of the customer, business name or person name, depending on the customer type.

vat_no.description: European VAT-registration number of the customer.

address.description: Address to the customer. Contains the following fields, with the same meanings as on a regular customer object.

careof.description: string (only one of careof or attention could be set, they cannot be combined)

attention.description: string (only one of careof or attention could be set, they cannot be combined)

item_no.description: Number of the item. If an item with the given number already exists in the items database, the data for that item will be used where it isn't overridden. If no item number is given, or a non-existing one is given, a single-use item is created, which only exists for the billogram it is used on. The max length for item_no is 30 characters IF the value is non-numeric, otherwise (if the value is numeric) the max value is 999999999.

count.description: The number (amount) of the item that is being invoiced. The value can be any whole or decimal number.

title.description: Primary (short) name for the item being invoiced.

description.description: Free-form description text for the item being invoiced.

unit.description: Unit of measure for the item. See the primary item structure for the valid values..

price.description: Cost per unit of the item. This value may be zero.

vat.description: VAT rate for the item being invoiced. This must be a numeric value between 0 and 100. See the primary item structure for the valid values.

discount.description: Discount to be applied to the total (ex. VAT) sum for the item, given in the invoicing currency.

income_account.description: Account number for payments received for this item. If left out or blank, the item uses the default account set up. If the value is blank or null, the default income account will be populated to the field when the billogram is attested.

vat_account.description: Account number for VAT payments received for this item. If left out or blank, the item uses the default account set up. If the value is blank or null, the default income account will be populated to the field when the billogram is attested.

objects.description: This is for objects and dimensions in accounting. Swedish: Objektredovisning  resultatenheter, dimensioner) Array of the bookkeeping objects and dimensions that are connected to this item (and in turn, this income account ). This is only needed if you need very specific bookkeeping. For each object in the list, the following parameters should be specified.

dimension_id.description: Dimension for your object, the values 1-19 may be used, but are reserved for standardized dimensions (for example 1 is 'Avdelning / kostnadsstlle / resultatenhet', 7 is 'Anstlld / anstllningsnummer'). Values over 20 should have a custom dimension_name set. Some bookkeeping applications require the dimension_id to be a numeric value between 1 and 999999. dimension_id and object_id are required for each object.

object_id.description: An identifier for this object. Some bookkeeping applications require the object_id to be a numeric value between 1 and 999999. dimension_id and object_id are required for each object.

dimension_name.description: A description for the dimension_id. Values over 20 may have a custom dimension_name set. If your dimension_id is 1-19, the dimension_name field will be ignored and the standardized name will be used. The latest submitted dimension_name will be saved for the specificed dimension_id.

object_name.description: A description for the object_id. The latest submitted object_name will be saved for the specificed object_id.

rotavdrag.description: Amount to deduct from the invoiced amount under ROT/RUT deduction rules, given in the invoicing currency. The exact rules for these deductions are outside the scope of this documentation.
Amount to deduct from the invoiced amount under ROT/RUT deduction rules, given in the invoicing currency. The exact rules for these deductions are outside the scope of this documentation.

rotavdrag_personal_number.description: Swedish personal number of the individual eligible for the tax deduction.

rotavdrag_description.description: Description of services invoiced for which the deduction is based on.

rotavdrag_housing_association_org_no.description: Housing association org. no. for deduction.

reversed_vat.description: Whether to use Swedish reversed VAT payment rules for this invoice.

autogiro_betalarnummer.description: The ID number that identifies the payer in the Autogiro system. It follows BGC format (numeric, max 16 characters).

autogiro_payment_date.description: Date on which the due amount is going to be withdrawn from payer's account

autogiro_status.description: Current status of the Autogiro payment for the Billogram. Will be null if autogiro is disabled. If enabled, status can be any of the following statuses unattested, scheduled, processing, successful or failed

autogiro_full_status.description: Extra information in case autogiro_status is failed

autogiro_total_sum.description: Amount to be withdrawn from payer's account.

efaktura_recipient_identifier.description: E-faktura recipient identifier, sometimes referred to as the FMI (fakturamottagaridentitet). Should be in the format YYYYMMDDXXXX.BANK.SE for individuals or individual companies or 00XXXXXXXXXX.BANK.SE for companies with organization number (06XXXXXXXXXX.SBF.SE for companies using Swedbank) where 'BANK' would be replaced by the bank_code. You may either submit this value or a combination of efaktura_recipient_type, efaktura_recipient_bank_name, efaktura_recipient_bank_id, efaktura_recipient_bank_code, efaktura_recipient_id_number. The remaining values will be calculated automatically. We recommend users to either only submit the efaktura_recipient_identifier or both efaktura_recipient_id_number + efaktura_recipient_bank_code to avoid errors.

efaktura_recipient_type.description: E-faktura recipient type, wether the recipient is an individual or a company. One of the following values: individual, company

efaktura_recipient_bank_name.description: E-faktura recipient's fully qualified bank name.

efaktura_recipient_bank_id.description: E-faktura recipient's bank's internal id, may differ if the recipient is an individual or a company. The numeric bank id is used in some e-faktura formats (for example BGCInvoice).

efaktura_recipient_bank_code.description: E-faktura recipient's bank's internal code, may differ if the recipient is an individual or a company.

efaktura_recipient_id_number.description: E-faktura recipient's id number or organization number. (Recommended 12 digits for individuals or individual companies, 10 digits for companies)

efaktura_requested_amount.description: The default amount to be paid when an E-faktura is viewed in the recipients internet bank (the amount can always be changed by the recipient though). If left as null (recommended) the invoice's amount to be paid will be the default specified amount. This value may not be changed after the E-faktura has been sent to the recipient.

objtyp.description: Type of object (Objektstyp). Valid values are 1 (Lgenhet/Villa utan eluppvrmning), 2 (Villa med eluppvrmning) or 3 (vrigt).

faktforb.description: Consumption on invoice (Frbrukning p faktura) specified in kWh.

faktfrek.description: Frequency of invoicing (Fakturafrekvens) in months. If you would send invoices every month the value would be 1. For bi-monthly the value would be 2. Quarterly is 3, etc.
